  "details": "Sparx Pro Cloud Server requires authentication based on requested URL. An attacker can omit the \"model\" query parameter and send the model name only in the binary blob in POST request allowing SQL query execution without authentication.\n\nThe vendor was notified early about this vulnerability, but didn't respond with the details of vulnerability or vulnerable version range. Only version 6.1 (build 167) and below were tested and confirmed as vulnerable, other versions were not tested and might also be vulnerable.",
